quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  97,1,"Verily, We have sent it (this Qur’ân) down in the night of Al-Qadr (Decree).",footnotes:337652:1
  97,2,"And what will make you know what the night of Al-Qadr (Decree) is?"
  97,3,"The night of Al-Qadr (Decree) is better than a thousand months (i.e. worshipping Allâh in that night is better than worshipping Him a thousand months, i.e. 83 years and 4 months)."
  97,4,"Therein descend the angels and the Rûh [Jibrîl (Gabrîl)] by Allâh’s Permission with all Decrees,"
  97,5,"(All that night), there is Peace (and Goodness from Allâh to His believing slaves) until the appearance of dawn.",footnotes:337655:1
